# .pubfiles — defines what gets published to GitHub for project: justinjanson
# Managed manually. Run 'pubcheck' to preview, 'gitpublish' to publish.
#
# Rules:
#   - One entry per line. Blank lines and # comments are ignored.
#   - Relative paths are resolved from this file's directory.
#   - Absolute paths are copied by basename (Dockerfile, stack.yml, etc.)
#   - Directories are copied recursively.
#   - Glob patterns are supported (e.g. ./src/**/*.py)
#
# Examples:
#   ./src/
#   ./README.md
#   /mnt/hostess/media/projects/dockerfiles/justinjanson/Dockerfile
#   /mnt/hostess/media/projects/homelab/stacks/justinjanson.yml

./
/mnt/hostess/media/projects/homelab/stacks/justinjanson.yml
/mnt/hostess/media/projects/webdev/justinjanson.com/html/*.*
/mnt/hostess/media/projects/webdev/justinjanson.com/html/assets/style.css
